Note:
Runa Standard Library: DefaultDict (Dictionary with Default Values)

Provides a dictionary that automatically creates default values for missing keys,
essential for AI-to-AI communication where default behaviors, fallback values,
and automatic initialization patterns are common.

Advanced features include:
- Automatic default value creation for missing keys
- Factory functions for complex default generation
- Nested default dictionaries for hierarchical data
- Memory-efficient lazy initialization
- Specialized factories for common types
:End Note

Type called "DefaultDict":
    data as Dictionary[String, Any]
    default_value as Any
    factory_type as String

Process called "create_default_dict" that returns DefaultDict:
    Return dictionary with:
        data as dictionary with:
        default_value as None
        factory_type as "none"

